onal results. Entropy profiles beyond R500\nclosely follow the predictions for the gravitational collapse of structures.\nThe scatter in all thermodynamical quantities reaches a minimum in the range\n[0.2-0.8] R500 and increases outwards. Somewhat surprisingly, we find that\npressure is substantially more scattered than temperature and density. Our\nresults indicate that once accreting substructures are properly excised, the\nproperties of the ICM beyond the cooling region R > 0.3 R500) follow remarkably\nwell the predictions of simple gravitational collapse and require little\nnon-gravitational corrections.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Apr 2018 18:07:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Oct 2018 14:59:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-09"}
